{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place ginger in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr> Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add pineapple and chop <nobr>4 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Add lime\/lemon juice and jam sugar and cook <nobr>14 min\/100°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Test for a set (see tip), transfer to 2 prepared jam jars with twist-off lids (à 500 g) – see tip – and close immediately. Turn upside down and allow to stand on lid for 5 minutes, then turn back upright and allow to cool. Store in a cool, dry place."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["25 g fresh ginger root, peeled and thinly sliced","750 g pineapple, fresh, cut into pieces","25 g lime juice","250 g jam sugar 3:1"]}],"id":"r126685","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-WM7yVlvhhPU\/XZWYgg97qmI\/AAAAAAAAd_Q\/nmxbr8iw-3wUii0xtoI2BSfnlx5Bw6NqgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_CFNRfLiNgzIKDWzN.png","title":"Pineapple and ginger jam","publishedAt":"2017-08-08T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2 g","fat":"0 g","uom":"per 1 jar","carbohydrates":"171 g","calories":"3017 kJ \/ 714 kcal"},"usefulItems":"jars with twist-off lids","hintsAndTricks":["<strong>Testing for a set<\/strong>: Place a small plate in freezer (<nobr>5–10 minutes<\/nobr>) before you begin making jam. Place a spoonful of jam on the cold plate, allow to cool and press lightly with your finger. If the jam wrinkles, it is ready. If not, allow to cook for a further <nobr>2 minutes<\/nobr> and repeat test.","To ensure the jam keeps for as long as possible, wash the jars thoroughly and dry in a warm oven or wash in the dishwasher. Transfer the jam to the jars while they are still warm.","The pineapple and ginger jam keeps for up to <nobr>6 months<\/nobr> when unopened and stored in a cool, dry place."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","40m","2 jars"]}